'''Daniel Jonathan Svensson''' (born 12 February 2002) is a Swedish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[central midfielder]] or [[left-back]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[Borussia Dortmund]] and the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].

==Club career==
On 3 February 2025, Svensson joined [[Borussia Dortmund]] in Germany on loan from [[FC Nordsjælland|Nordsjælland]] with an option to buy.<ref>{{Cite web |title=BVB sign Daniel Svensson on loan |publisher=Borussia Dortmund|url=https://www.bvb.de/de/en/news/news-overview/news.html/2025/2/3/BVB-sign-Daniel-Svensson-on-loan.html |access-date=2025-02-03 |website=www.bvb.de}}</ref> On 20 April, he scored his first goal for Dortmund in a 3–2 victory over [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bvb.de/de/de/aktuelles/news/news.html/2025/4/20/32-nach-01-BVB-bejubelt-drei-Big-Points.html |title=3:2 nach 0:1 – BVB bejubelt drei Big-Points |publisher=Borussia Dortmund |language=de |date=20 April 2025 }}</ref>

After a successful loan spell, he joined on a permanent contract on 14 May 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |title=BVB announce permanent signing of Daniel Svensson|publisher=Borussia Dortmund|url=https://www.bvb.de/de/en/news/news-overview/news.html/2025/5/14/BVB-announce-permanent-signing-of-Daniel-Svensson.html |access-date=2025-06-26 |website=www.bvb.de}}</ref> Later that year, on 1 October, he netted his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal in a 4–1 win over [[Athletic Bilbao]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Emons |first=Michael |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c784vgq71eet |title=Borussia Dortmund 4–1 Athletic Club |publisher=BBC Sport |date=1 October 2025 }}</ref>

== International career ==
Svensson made his full international debut for the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]] on 14 October 2024, replacing [[Yasin Ayari]] in the 89th minute of a [[UEFA Nations League]] game against [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]] which Sweden won 3–0.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Estonia vs. Sweden |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/matchfakta/estland-sverige-landskamper-herr-senior/5791238/ |website=SvFF}}</ref>

On 12 May 2026, Svensson was named in the Sweden squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-12 |title=Mystiskt inlägg efter petningen |url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/landslaget/har-ar-sveriges-trupp-till-fotbolls-vm-2026/ |access-date=2026-05-15 |website=www.expressen.se |language=sv}}</ref>

